@tarkeke Portal isn't FPS, and it's technically a platformer.

I was speaking to a guy who said this game was boring o.O

He claims that he has beaten both games, and Mario Galaxy was repetitive to him. The level design makes you never put down the controller because it's very creative. Someone who actually played it will mostly agree with this. I honestly don't think he finished Portal since that one requires a lot of physics, if he was really "bored" from this game...

@scikoolaid 

That reminds me of why I kinda like Banjo Kazooie more than Mario 64. You could accomplish everything in one run without having to be kicked out of the level as a way to extend game play. Though I can see why it was done in the mario games since some stars are event based and change the level pretty drastically like in mario sunshine where a later level is covered in lava pollution and you don't have fludd with you 

I love mario, but mario galaxy had too many things I didn't like.

@KILLERMILLER250 

I'd rather not play either of those. Super Meat Boy was easily the best Platformer this gen. It's pretty sad when an indie game ends up being far better than these bloated big budget games. Mario Galaxy was the first game in the main series that I didn't enjoy playing. 

The shortage of good platformers this gen is pretty depressing at least Rayman Origins looks good though.
